<plot>An illuminating spotlight on the dark psychological corners of the life of Hollywood's greatest icon, "My Marilyn" reveals a complex woman set alongside the men of power she pursued with unrelenting abandon, who challenged the conventions of her time of what a woman should be in mind, body and career. "My Marilyn" is a passionate and revealing choreography of imagery and stories about the life, loves and death of the "Eternal Feminine," from the point of view of people who have devoted a significant part of their lives to communicating her true story.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?384432</url></doc>
